# Rust build artifacts
/target
# The client lives in its own cargo workspace (crates/client-app) with its own
# target dir; ignore it too (the root `/target` only covers the server workspace).
/crates/client-app/target
**/*.rs.bk

# Local demo staging (built .exe binaries + demo data) — not source, never committed
/dist/

# Frontend redesign drops + scratch handed in/out during UI work
/maxsecu-frontend*.zip
/clipboard-*.png
/install-design.ps1

# Never commit secrets. The Dropbox token / app secret and the offline D5/D6
# key material are injected at runtime / kept air-gapped (DESIGN.md §16.6,
# stack.md §5.1) — they must never land in the repo.
*.secret
*.token
secrets/
.env
.env.*

# OS / editor noise
Thumbs.db
.DS_Store

# Reproducible-build scratch dirs (scripts/reproducible-build.*)
target-repro-a/
target-repro-b/

# Brainstorming visual-companion scratch (superpowers)
.superpowers/

# Vendored static ffmpeg for the universal-video-ingest feature (D-1). The binary
# is FETCHED (scripts/fetch-ffmpeg.ps1) and its SHA-256 is pinned in source
# (vendor/ffmpeg/README.md + crates/client-app/src/ffmpeg_bin.rs); the bytes
# themselves are never committed.
/vendor/ffmpeg/*.exe
/vendor/ffmpeg/*.zip

# Compile-time recovery-account pubkey PIN. Written by `maxsecu-setup` (T14) and
# baked into the client by `crates/client-app/build.rs` via a generated const;
# the bytes are a per-deployment trust anchor and are never committed. Absent →
# the build fails closed (or emits a labelled test pin under `--features
# unpinned-dev`). See `crates/client-app/src/recovery_pin.rs`.
/crates/client-app/recovery_pin.bin
